[
  {
    "text": "By the Lord is enveloped all this, whatever moves in this moving world. Through such renunciation support yourself. Covet no one's wealth.",
    "scripture": "Isha Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 1,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "atman"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "a8852d83950b6a83"
  },
  {
    "text": "Performing works in this world, one should desire to live a hundred years. There is no other way for you than this. In this way, action does not cling to a person.",
    "scripture": "Isha Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 2,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "428be45f44900be9"
  },
  {
    "text": "There are those worlds called the worlds of the demons, covered with blind darkness. To them go after death those who slay the Self.",
    "scripture": "Isha Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 3,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "atman",
      "death",
      "maya"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "f7e24e52d21f452d"
  },
  {
    "text": "That one, though never stirring, is swifter than thought. The senses do not reach it; it has gone before. Standing still, it outstrips others that run. In it the all-pervading air supports the activities of beings.",
    "scripture": "Isha Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 4,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "1e7f251a1cf790af"
  },
  {
    "text": "It moves and it moves not. It is far and it is near. It is within all this, and it is also outside all this.",
    "scripture": "Isha Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 5,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "61f003bdf507ec1b"
  },
  {
    "text": "He who beholds all beings in the Self, and the Self in all beings, no longer hates anything.",
    "scripture": "Isha Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 6,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "atman"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "72658e63c9d94dc0"
  },
  {
    "text": "For one who knows, in whom all beings have become the Self, what delusion, what sorrow can there be when he sees this oneness?",
    "scripture": "Isha Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 7,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "atman",
      "knowledge"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "0cb734c471611f8e"
  },
  {
    "text": "He has spread out into all things — the radiant, bodiless, free from injury, free from sinews, pure, untouched by evil. He, the seer, the thinker, all-pervading, self-existent, has rightly assigned the things eternally for all the years to come.",
    "scripture": "Isha Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 8,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "atman",
      "liberation"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "7115a5ba5ce5e522"
  },
  {
    "text": "Into blinding darkness enter those who worship ignorance; into greater darkness, as it were, those who delight in knowledge alone.",
    "scripture": "Isha Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 9,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "knowledge",
      "meditation",
      "maya"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "7163a6f1f0363e6c"
  },
  {
    "text": "One thing, they say, is reached by knowledge; another, they say, by ignorance. So we have heard from the wise who taught us this.",
    "scripture": "Isha Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 10,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "knowledge",
      "maya"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "5cfe866f4f1b876c"
  },
  {
    "text": "He who knows together both knowledge and ignorance — by ignorance crosses over death, by knowledge attains the immortal.",
    "scripture": "Isha Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 11,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "death",
      "knowledge",
      "maya"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "6882106771c3e14c"
  },
  {
    "text": "Into blinding darkness enter those who worship the unmanifest; into greater darkness, as it were, those who delight in the manifest.",
    "scripture": "Isha Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 12,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "meditation",
      "creation",
      "maya"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "6968dfc67c61a078"
  },
  {
    "text": "One thing, they say, is reached by the manifest; another, they say, by the unmanifest. So we have heard from the wise who taught us this.",
    "scripture": "Isha Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 13,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "creation"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "3c24ce87c8527b6e"
  },
  {
    "text": "He who knows together both the manifest and the unmanifest — by the unmanifest crosses over death, by the manifest attains the immortal.",
    "scripture": "Isha Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 14,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "death",
      "knowledge",
      "creation"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "1a75cdb6be85debe"
  },
  {
    "text": "The face of the True is hidden by a golden disc. Unveil it, O Pushan, that I, whose dharma is truth, may behold.",
    "scripture": "Isha Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 15,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "7ae364544fe09e94"
  },
  {
    "text": "O Pushan, sole seer, controller of all, sun, son of Prajapati, dispose your rays, gather up your radiance. The light which is your fairest form, that I see. He, that being, am I.",
    "scripture": "Isha Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 16,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "5505826a08a8dac9"
  },
  {
    "text": "May the breath go to the immortal breath; the body then ends in ashes. Aum. Mind, remember; what was done, remember. Mind, remember; what was done, remember.",
    "scripture": "Isha Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 17,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "death"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "07010bac99af0ea0"
  },
  {
    "text": "Agni, lead us by a good path to wealth, O God who knows all our deeds. Remove from us the crooked sin. We would offer you the fullest praise.",
    "scripture": "Isha Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 18,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
